    // the final value for any $x$ will be the minimum element $d$ in the set of reachable values that divides $x$.

    // Let's identify all unique values $U$ in `nums`.
    // We want to find, for each $u \in U$, the smallest reachable value $r(u)$.
    // Initially, $r(u) = u$.
