    // If $g$ is present in $nums$, all elements become $g$.
    // If $g$ is not present, but there is $d$ in $nums$ such that $d$ is the smallest element dividing $g$ (which is impossible if $d>1$), then we are stuck.

    // The final value for any $x$ is the smallest element $d$ in the original array such that $d$ divides $x$,
    // provided $d$ is the minimum among all such divisors that can propagate.

    // Let $S$ be the set of unique elements in `nums`.
    // For each $x \in nums$, the resulting value $x'$ will be $\min \{ d \in S \mid d \text{ divides } x \text{ and } d \text{ is irreducible} \}$.

