    // Simpler approach:
    // 1. Collect all unique elements $U$.
    // 2. Sort $U$: $u_1 < u_2 < \ldots < u_k$.
    // 3. For each $u_i$, determine its final minimal value $m_i$.
    //    $m_i$ starts at $u_i$.
    //    Iterate $j$ from $1$ to $i-1$:
    //      If $u_i \% u_j == 0$:
    //        $m_i = \min(m_i, m_j)$. (Since $u_j$ can be reduced to $m_j$, and $m_j$ divides $u_j$, it divides $u_i$).
